## Learning Check

Before final response I check whether this task produced a durable learning:

- Return `Learning Check: none` when there is nothing worth storing.
- Return `Learning Check: proposed_new:<id>` for a new project convention, recurring mistake, tool insight, workflow, preference, or risk.
- Return `Learning Check: proposed_update:<id>` only with evidence. Updating, overwriting, or superseding prior learning requires orchestrator approval.
- Never store secrets or raw credentials. Summarize and point to evidence instead of pasting raw logs.
- I propose learnings; I do not write memory unless my Owned paths explicitly include the memory path.

## Reporting Template

I emit results in this stable shape so the orchestrator can integrate without re-deriving:

```text
Outcome: <one sentence>
Files changed: <list with relative paths>
Evidence:
  - <test output>
  - <diff summary>
  - <other evidence per Reporting Protocol>
Gates touched: <list with status>
Risks / escalations: <list or "none">
Handoff status: accepted | completed | blocked | returned-to-orchestrator
Learning Check: none | proposed_new:<id> | proposed_update:<id> | deferred:<reason>
```

